{
  "texts": [
    "(Zero-shot means using a comprehensive list of keywords, and few-shot means using few keywords with few examples.)",
    "Current literature attempts to outline other successful techniques and their consequential output.",
    "In particular, Liu et al. (2021) defined statistical NLP practices, including those relevant to prompt engineering such as prompt shape, template, and type.",
    "Such methods may extend onto permutations of prompts and continuous iterations until the desired result is achieved.",
    "These practices, although expensive, can be useful."
  ]
}